<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 3:07PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Trumbull,
southeastern Geauga and southern Ashtabula Counties through 345 PM
EDT...
At 306 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
North Bloomfield, or 16 miles north of Warren, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cortland, Middlefield, Kinsman, North Bloomfield, Orwell, West
Farmington, Bristolville, Parkman, Huntsburg, Mecca, Johnston,
Orangeville and Yankee Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
